    "content": "* VPFA: How do we want to rearrange the office? (Want to hand this over to Steffen now)\n* Steffen accepts this.\n* VPFA: Can I get a new safe? I can’t open the old one…does anyone wanna try?\n* VP Phil: Eng ball tickets are currently a solid $85 (typical prices), however to get it down to $60, we would have to supplement around 7.5k estimated. Do we think it’s worth it to start ticket sales at that price and if we don’t get that in sponsorships, we supplement that ourselves?\n* Gross on Eng Ball is usually -7.5k, so paying this difference could provide a more accessible event!\n* Eric: Loss in the past doesn’t have to be repeated.\n* Some loss could be accessible.\n* Eric: Solid sponsorships could bridge the difference.\n* Sydney: What is the timeframe on early bird vs regular ticket?\n* Zoe: Still in talks with Studio 44\n* Sydney: Early birds could be $60, but only available for a day, then hype them up to the max.\n* Eric: Possibly a gamble if too much is lost on early bird tickets.\n* Brooke: Early bird just before exams\n* Eric: Raffle tickets could be an early bird entry\n* Limited early bird tickets could be an incentive\n* Raffle winnings could be white covies, exclusive hard hats,\n* Cyrus: Discount for Execs, officers, etc?\n* Zoe: Early bird discount is about as good as ESS affiliates are getting.\n* This event will be applied for in Winter semester EEF\n* A certain set amount is set for donation each year, as well as auction gains.\n* Zoe: Promotion is key for this year, and lower ticket prices could boost this.\n* VP Social : Saunders Fright Fest on the low deal",
